From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: wosnxn123 <wosnxn123@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 4 Jul 2026 16:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add Vanilla-like experience config

Adds a single master toggle (config/canvas-server.yml ->
vanilla-like-experience.enabled) that restores vanilla mechanics Paper/Folia
changed. Ported from Lophine's 0048 patch, adapted to Canvas's config system
(GlobalConfiguration) and Canvas's actual NMS context.

Restores: tripwire hook placement validation bypass (string dup farms /
shua xian ji), TNT & sand duping via piston desync, permanent block break
exploits, headless pistons, vanilla mob spawning, unlimited entity collisions,
player cramming damage, vanilla phantom/insomnia behavior, no TNT-per-tick
limit, and vanilla hopper/bee/item-merge/end-portal-teleport behavior.
When disabled, Paper/Folia per-mechanic configs apply as normal.

diff --git a/ca/spottedleaf/moonrise/paper/PaperHooks.java b/ca/spottedleaf/moonrise/paper/PaperHooks.java
--- a/ca/spottedleaf/moonrise/paper/PaperHooks.java
+++ b/ca/spottedleaf/moonrise/paper/PaperHooks.java
@@ -204,6 +204,11 @@ public class PaperHooks extends BaseChunkSystemHooks implements PlatformHooks {

     @Override
     public int configMaxAutoSavePerTick(final ServerLevel world) {
+        // Canvas start - vanilla-like experience
+        if (io.canvasmc.canvas.GlobalConfiguration.getInstance().vanillaLikeExperience.enabled) {
+            return 200;
+        }
+        // Canvas end - vanilla-like experience
         return world.paperConfig().chunks.maxAutoSaveChunksPerTick;
     }

